1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Nf3 d5 6. Bd2 Re8 7. Qc2 {
transposes to the game.} b6 {Black didn't want to enter known and theoretical
paths and instead comes up with something original. However, this idea has a
serious drawback.} 8. a3 Bf8 9. e4 $1 {White punishes Black by striking in the
centre immediately.} dxe4 10. Nxe4 Nbd7 11. Bd3 Bb7 12. Neg5 $1 g6 13. O-O-O
$40 {Most of White's pieces are concentrated towards the black king, which
eases his attack and makes it difficult to defend over the board.} h6 (13...
Bxf3 14. gxf3 c5 15. h4 $40) 14. h4 $1 {White brings as many attackers as
possible.} Bg7 15. h5 $1 hxg5 (15... gxh5 16. Nh7 $16) 16. hxg6 $18 {White has
more attackers than Black has defenders and is already close to winning here.}
Bxf3 (16... fxg6 17. Bxg6 Nf8 18. Ne5 {[%cal Rd2g5,Rg6f7]}) 17. gxf7+ Kxf7 18.
Bg6+ Kf8 19. gxf3 Re7 20. Bxg5 c5 21. Rh4 ({Now best would have been} 21. d5 $1
{, increasing the pressure to a breaking point. But the text move was also
good enough to convert the position to a full point.} exd5 22. cxd5 {[%cal
Rd5d6,Rg5d8,Rc2f5,Ye1e8]}) 21... cxd4 22. Rhxd4 Rc8 23. Qd2 Qc7 24. Kb1 Kg8 25.
Qe2 Nf8 26. Bc2 Rf7 27. Rg1 Qh2 28. Qe1 N6d7 29. Rh4 Qe5 30. Qc1 Qe2 31. Bh6
Rc7 32. Bxg7 Rxg7 33. Rxg7+ Kxg7 34. Qg5+ Kf7 35. Bg6+ {Rakhmanov-Bocharov
2019 1-0} *

