Black's hanging pawns.} (15. Qh5 {Going for an all-out attack.} g6 (15... h6 $6
16. Rf3 $40 {[%cal Gf3g3,Yh5f5]}) 16. Qf3 {This is the critical position in
this variation. Black's best way to handle it is to keep all the threats alive
by playing} Bg7 $5 $146 {Black's bishop won't come under attack when White
captures on d5. Now any move by White has some drawback.} (16... cxd4 17. Nxd5
$16 dxe3 (17... Bg7 18. e4 $16) 18. Nxf6+ Qxf6 19. Bc3 $36 {[%csl Gc3][%cal
Ra1h8,Yf4f5]}) (16... Nb4 17. Bb1 cxd4 {Grabbing the pawn is not a good idea
here!} 18. exd4 Bxd4+ 19. Kh1 Rc8 (19... Nc6 $6 20. f5 $40 Be5 21. Qh3 Qd6 22.
