{1-0 (40) Hawkins,J (2511) -Cobb, J (2424) Leeds ENG 2013}) 14... cxd4 (14...
b5 15. Bf5 b4 16. Nxd7 Nxd7 17. Na4 $16) 15. exd4 b5 16. a3 $36 (16. Bh4 {
is also possible.})) (11... Nxe5 12. dxe5 Ne4 13. Bc1 {[%cal Gf2f3,Gc3e2,Gd3h7]
The engine comes up with a brilliant move. The point being, after Black takes
on c3, White always has the option of Bc1-a3 at some point.} (13. Bxe4 dxe4 14.
Rfd1 Bxc3 15. Bxc3 Qe7 16. Rd2 Rad8 17. Rad1 $11 {1/2-1/2 (22) Jussupow, A 
