1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd2 d6 {Black just wants to take
White from the theoretical zone and play over-the-board chess. Here we should
not play automatic moves but think logically and meet the positional
requirements.} (5... Re8 6. Bd3 b6 7. Nf3 Bb7 8. O-O c5 9. a3 {We almost
always play this whenever Black plays opts for c5.} Ba5 {As always Black must
watch for White's next move when playing Ba5.} 10. b4 $1 cxb4 11. Nb5 Bxf3 12.
Qxf3 Nc6 13. Nd6 $36 {1-0 (36) Aleksandrov,A (2602)-Shengelia,D (2512) Batumi
2018}) (5... d5 6. Nf3 Re8 7. Qc2 {[%emt 0:00:04] This was already analysed in
model game 4.}) 6. Bd3 c5 (6... e5 7. Nge2 {Developing the knight to f3 is
ruled out because of e5-e4.} Re8 (7... Qe7 8. O-O Bxc3 9. Nxc3 e4 10. Bc2 Bg4
11. f3 exf3 12. gxf3 Bh3 13. Rf2 $16 {1-0 (30) Heberla, B (2546)-Malec, S 
(2132) Warsaw POL 2018}) (7... exd4 8. exd4 d5 9. cxd5 Nxd5 10. O-O Nc6 11. a3
Be7 12. Qc2 $14 {1/2-1/2 (57) Aczel, G (2540)-Ruck, R (2524) Ajka HUN 2019}) 8.
O-O Nbd7 9. a3 Bxc3 10. Nxc3 Nf8 (10... e4 11. Bc2 Nb6 12. b3 Bg4 13. f3 exf3
14. gxf3 Bh3 15. Rf2 $14 {0-1 (41) Cichocki, A (2330) -Romanishin, O (2550) MK
Cafe, Koszalin POL 1997}) 11. Qc2 Bg4 12. Ne4 c6 13. Nxf6+ Qxf6 14. Bc3 Qh6 15.
Rae1 Bh5 16. f3 f6 17. d5 Bf7 18. e4 $16 {1/2-1/2 (36) Adhiban,B (2639)
-Iturrizaga, E (2626) Khanty-Mansiysk RUS 2019}) 7. a3 Ba5 8. dxc5 $1 {White
clarifies the situation in the centre before hunting down Black's king.} dxc5
9. Qc2 Nc6 10. Nf3 {White just develops the pieces and keeps the opponent
guessing about his intentions of castling.} Bc7 (10... h6 11. O-O-O $1 $40 {
Most of White's pieces are well-positioned to create chaos on the board.} Qe7
12. Rhg1 Ng4 13. Be1 Rb8 14. h3 Nge5 15. Nxe5 Nxe5 16. Be2 a6 17. f4 Nc6 18.
Bf3 Na7 19. g4 $40 {1-0 (27) Zude,E (2381)-Rodriguez Ferraz,B (2175) Barcelona
ESP 2014}) 11. O-O-O g6 12. Ne4 $1 {Not only eliminating the important
defender but also vacating c3 for the bishop, to control the a1-h8 diagonal.}
Nxe4 13. Bxe4 Bd7 14. g4 e5 15. Rhg1 Qe7 16. Bd5 Rae8 17. h4 Kh8 18. Bc3 $40 {
[%cal Gc3h8,Gd5g8] 1-0 (27) Predke, A (2620)-Gajek, R (2481) Chennai IND 2019}
*

