1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd2 b6 6. Nf3 Bb7 7. Bd3 c5 (7... d6
8. O-O Nbd7 9. b3 $5 {Black will sooner or later take on c3, followed by Ne4.
Hence White plays a useful move so that Ne4 can be met with Bb2.} e5 {[%cal
Re5e4]} (9... Qe7 10. a3 Bxc3 11. Bxc3 Ne4 12. Bb2 f5 13. Nd2 {As always, it
is best to challenge the knight on e4 as soon as possible.} Nxd2 14. Qxd2 Rf6
15. f3 {[%csl Rb7,Gf3] A typical move, restricting Black's light-squared
bishop. After warding off Black's counterplay on the kingside, it is time to
create our own play on the queenside!} Re8 16. b4 $1 $14 {[%cal Ga3a4,Ga4a5]
1-0 (47) Sandipan,C (2554)-Elgersma,O (2171) Vlissingen NED 2018}) 10. Ne1 (10.
Bf5 $5 {is also possible.}) 10... Qe7 11. a3 Bxc3 12. Bxc3 exd4 13. exd4 Rae8
14. d5 Ne5 15. Nf3 Nxd3 16. Qxd3 Qe4 17. Qd2 $14 {[%csl Gc3][%cal Ra1h8] 1-0 
(35) Pratyusha,B (2265)-Lei Tingjie (2505) Shaoxing CHN 2019}) (7... Bxc3 8.
Bxc3 Ne4 9. Bxe4 $1 Bxe4 10. d5 $1 {[%csl Gc3][%cal Ra1h8] The point behind
the previous move.} c5 (10... exd5 11. Qd4 Qf6 (11... f6 12. cxd5 Qe7 13. Nd2
Bg6 14. h4 d6 15. h5 Bf7 16. h6 $18 {1-0 (36) Valenzuela Gomez,F (2406)
-Gallego Bergada,A (2173) Vila-seca ESP 2019}) 12. Qxf6 gxf6 13. Nd2 Re8 14.
Nxe4 dxe4 15. Bxf6 $14 {White's bishop is better than the black knight and
White can combine queenside and kingside play as Black's king is weak. White
won convincingly in 1-0 (31) Sandipan,C (2555) -Kishan,G (2024) Jammu IND 2018}
) (10... f6 11. Nd2 (11. Nh4 $5 {[%cal Gf2f3,Ge3e4,Yd1g4] was probably
stronger.}) 11... Bg6 12. h4 h6 13. h5 Bh7 14. e4 Qe7 15. O-O (15. Qe2 Na6 16.
O-O c6 $132 {1/2-1/2 (41) Muthaiah,A (2408)-Visakh Nr (2491) Mumbai IND 2019})
15... Na6 16. Re1 {[%csl Ge1][%cal Ye1e8,Ge1e3,Ge3g3] , with a slight edge for
White.}) 11. Nd2 Bg6 12. h4 $1 exd5 13. cxd5 h6 (13... Bd3 14. Qg4 f6 15. O-O-O
Qe7 16. Nb3 Ba6 17. e4 $36 {1-0 (39) Valenzuela Gomez, F (2373)-Iniyan,P (2497)
Sitges ESP 2019}) (13... f6 14. h5 Bd3 15. h6 g6 16. Nf3 (16. Qf3 d6 17. Ne4 $6
Nd7 $15 {0-1 (30) Shcherbine,A (2171)-Real de Azua, E (2445) Buenos Aires ARG
2009}) 16... Be4 (16... Ba6 17. Nh4 $1 $40) 17. Ng1 $1 {[%cal Rf2f3]} g5 (17...
Bxg2 18. Rh2 Be4 19. f3 $18 {[%csl Re4]}) 18. f3 Bg6 19. Nh3 $16 {[%csl Gc3,
Gh6][%cal Ge1g1,Gf3f4]}) (13... Qe7 14. Qf3 d6 15. h5 Bd3 16. h6 g6 17. Bf6 $16
{1/2-1/2 (57) Gogochuri,L (2155)-Gaprindashvili,V (2489) Tbilisi GEO 2007}) 14.
Qg4 h5 15. Qf3 Qe8 16. g4 f6 17. Rg1 $18 {[%csl Gg1][%cal Rg1g8] 1-0 (25)
Bluebaum,M (2619)-Zysk,R (2404) Zurich SUI 2019}) 8. a3 Bxc3 (8... Ba5 {
Black keeps the option of capturing on c3 at his convenience.} 9. O-O d6 (9...
d5 10. cxd5 cxd4 (10... Nxd5 $2 11. Nxd5 Bxd2 12. Nf4 Ba5 13. Qb1 $18 {[%cal
