}) 11. exd4 {[%cal Gb2b4]} Bxc3 12. bxc3 Qxd5 {[%csl Gc3,Gd4] White has a
typical hanging pawns structure and a lead in development.} 13. c4 {was
probably stronger.} (13. Re1 Nbd7 14. c4 Qc6 15. a4 Qd6 16. Bc3 Qf4 {1/2-1/2 
(63) Manolache,M (2518) -Filip,L (2432) Alba Iulia ROU 2018}) 13... Qh5 14. Ne5
$1 {Taking advantage of the fact that the knight is not on d7 or c6 to control
